## Design Notes

| Area | Decision |
|---|---|
| **Boundary values** | Tests explicitly cover days 364, 365 (inclusive), and 366 to pin down the exact cutoff |
| **Fixtures** | Parameterised customer fixtures keep test data DRY and readable |
| **`freeze_time`** | Eliminates flakiness from real-clock drift; all date assertions are deterministic |
| **Exception types** | Custom exception classes (`OutboundTransactionRestrictedError`, etc.) make assertion intent explicit |
| **Test classes** | Grouped by concern — status, restriction, transactions, workflow, rolling window, edge cases |
| **Mocking** | `patch.object` used only where external side-effects (notifications) need isolation |
| **Negative tests** | Cover null inputs, negative amounts, and orphaned accounts to guard against silent failures |

